    <stitle>HENDRICKSON SUSPENSION SYSTEMS - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SPRING LEAF SUSPENSIONS - U/UE, RT/RTE, RT2/RTE2 SERIES (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300624">Figure 24</hotlnk>)
            </title>
            <figure id="f0300624" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300624" filename="../figg03/G0300624.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Spring Leaf Suspensions - U/UE, RT/RTE, RT2/RTE2 Series</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.TORQUE ROD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.TORQUE ROD FRAME BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.BACKUP PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.TRANSVERSE TORQUE ROD FRAME BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.TRANSVERSE TORQUE ROD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.AXLE BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>7.REAR SPRING FRONT BRACKET DOUBLE LOCK BOLT STYLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>8.SPRING TOP PAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>9.TOP PAD HEX-HEAD BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>10.TOP PAD SETSCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>11.REAR SPRING REAR BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>12.REBOUND BOLT &#38; SPACER ASSY</callout1>
                    <callout1>13.AXLE STOP</callout1>
                    <callout1>14.CENTER BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>15.RT/RTE, RT2/RTE2 SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>16.U/UE SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>17.U-BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>18.SPRING CENTER BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>19.SPRING TOP PAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>20.SADDLE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>21.WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>22.TOP PAD NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>23.CROSS TUBE</callout1>
                    <callout1>24.BEAM</callout1>
                    <callout1>25.END BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>26.BEAM END ADAPTER ASSEMBLY, BAR PIN ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>27.SADDLE CAP STUD NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>28.WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>29.STUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>30.SADDLE CAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>31.LUBE FITTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>32.THRUST WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>33.SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>34.SLEEVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>35.BRONZE CENTER BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>36.RUBBER CENTER BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>37.SPRING EYE BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>38.DRAWKEY ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>39.PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>40.LUBE FITTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>41.REAR SPRING FRONT BRACKET, DRAWKEY STYLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>42.LOCK BOLT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the beams and axles rolled out from under the frame, securely support the spring
                    and saddle assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For double lock bolt spring brackets: Remove the rear spring front bracket lock bolts,
                    then drive out the spring bracket pin. Remove the rebound bolt and spacer from the rear spring rear
                    bracket, then lower the spring and saddle assembly from the spring brackets.
                </para>
                <para>Loosen the spring top pad set screws, and remove the top pad bolts and the top pad. Remove the
                    spring assembly from the saddle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>For drawkey spring brackets: Loosen the locknut on the drawkey enough to protect the threads, then
                strike the nut with a hammer to loosen the drawkey. Remove the drawkey and drive the spring pin out of
                the spring and spring bracket.
            </para>
            <para>Loosen the U-bolt nuts, and remove the spring assembly from the saddle.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the spring assembly from the frame and remove it from the jack.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
